**Severity:** High

**OWASP Top 10 2021 Category:** Broken Access Control

**Description:**

CVE-2013-0169 is a vulnerability in Apache Http Server that allows an unauthenticated remote attacker to gain access to sensitive files. An attacker can exploit this vulnerability by sending a specially crafted request to the server. Successful exploitation of this vulnerability could allow the attacker to view sensitive information, such as user credentials or website content.

**Solution:**

To fix this issue, you can apply the following patch provided by Apache:

https://httpd.apache.org/security/vulnerabilities_2_4.html#CVE-2013-0169

Additionally, you can take the following steps to mitigate the risk of this vulnerability:

* Limit access to the sensitive files by configuring appropriate file permissions.
* Use a firewall to block unauthorized access to the server.
* Regularly update the Apache Http Server software to the latest version.
